From 3cef484defc012921d4d7cf64ebef5e3bea5ac8f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DOSKUTSU NXEngine Port <services.claude@accounts.ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:52:57 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 5/9] [DOSKUTSU] renderer: runtime lock to 320x240 fullscreen
 on DOS
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: NXEngine-evo's getResolutions() table includes 4:3 modes
from 320x240 up through 1600x1200 plus widescreen modes up to 3840x2160.
On the doskutsu DOS target (g2k reference: ATI Mach64 PCI + M64VBE.COM
VESA 1.2+ BIOS, Pentium OverDrive 83 MHz, 48 MB RAM), only 320x240 is
both reliably negotiable through SDL3-DOS's video backend AND fast enough
to maintain the engine's framerate budget. Selecting any other entry from
the table either fails to set the VESA mode or drops below playable.

Per CLAUDE.md § Critical Rules / NXEngine-evo specifics + locked decision
#5 in PLAN.md, the resolution table is preserved (compiled in) for
possible future revisit (DOSBox-X testing of other modes; CRT vs LCD
trade-offs); the lock is a runtime override in initVideo, not a code
removal.

Site: src/graphics/Renderer.cpp `Renderer::initVideo()`.

Approach (two NXE_DOS-gated blocks):

1. **Window flag**: add `SDL_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN` to window_flags before
   SDL_CreateWindow. Fullscreen is the only sensible mode under DOS — there
   is no windowing system to draw a windowed-mode chrome around the game.
   (SDL3 will treat the flag identically; the windowed/fullscreen bit
   survives the 0010 SDL3 migration unchanged.)

2. **Resolution override**: after the `res[_current_res]` lookup, override
   width / height / scale / screenHeight / screenWidth / widescreen with
   320x240 / 1 / 240 / 320 / false. Done after the upstream lookup rather
   than instead of it so that any settings persistence still reads /
   writes a valid index without us needing to touch settings.cpp.

Non-DOS builds: both blocks `#ifdef NXE_DOS`-out cleanly; Linux / macOS /
Windows native users get the unchanged upstream resolution-selection path.

Future work (not this patch): if Phase 9 hardware-tier work needs to
unlock 8bpp indexed mode (Tier 3 stretch), the resolution lock and the
pixel-format choice are independent — this patch doesn't constrain the
8bpp work.
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index a71f7f1..d621e90 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -68,6 +68,13 @@ bool Renderer::isWindowVisible()
 bool Renderer::initVideo()
 {
   uint32_t window_flags = SDL_WINDOW_SHOWN;
+#ifdef NXE_DOS
+  // DOS lock: force 320x240 fullscreen regardless of which res index the user
+  // (or the settings file) selected. The widescreen / HD entries in
+  // getResolutions() remain compiled in for possible future use per CLAUDE.md
+  // locked decision #5 — we don't rip the table out, we just skip past it.
+  window_flags |= SDL_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN;
+#endif
 
   const NXE::Graphics::gres_t *res = getResolutions(true);
 
@@ -78,6 +85,21 @@ bool Renderer::initVideo()
   screenWidth  = res[_current_res].base_width;
   widescreen   = res[_current_res].widescreen;
 
+#ifdef NXE_DOS
+  // Override whatever resolution the settings asked for. 320x240 is the only
+  // VESA mode the SDL3-DOS backend can reliably negotiate on the reference
+  // hardware (ATI Mach64 + M64VBE.COM); other modes either fail to set or
+  // run too slow to be playable. scale=1 keeps the renderer in the cheap
+  // 1:1 path (Phase 9 perf work). widescreen=false preserves the engine's
+  // native 4:3 viewport.
+  width        = 320;
+  height       = 240;
+  scale        = 1;
+  screenHeight = 240;
+  screenWidth  = 320;
+  widescreen   = false;
+#endif
+
   if (_window)
   {
     LOG_WARN("second call to Renderer::InitVideo()");
